|GKO====================================================================
                         |WKOGarou Guild : Equipment
|GKO====================================================================
|YKOWhile a wolf has no need for sword or shirt, a Garou who decides
to hunt in man or crinos form will naturally desire equipment to
make the hunt easier. As a creature of Gaea, however, a Garou
must take great care to stay away from equipment that the beloved
goddess hates and abhors. A Garou using such equipment will lose
all touch with Gaea and thus be unable to utilize any abilities.

|CKBWeapon Restrictions:
|WKO--------------------
|RKOA Garou may not use magical weapons of any kind.
A Garou may not use missile weapons of any kind.
A Garou may not use silver weapons of any kind.
A Garou may not use metallic weapons of any kind.

|BKOException: A Garou may use metallic polearm weapons provided they
           are not magical or composed of silver.

|CKBArmor Restrictions:
|WKO-------------------
|RKOA Garou may not wear magical armor of any kind.
A Garou may not wear silver armor of any kind.
A Garou may not wear metallic armor of any kind.
A Garou may not wear plate-type armor of any kind.

|BKOException: A Garou may use plate and/or metallic finger and amulet
           class armor provided such is not magical or silver.

|CKBCrinos Restrictions:
|WKO--------------------
|YKOSince crinos are massive and powerful beasts, there are additional
restrictions to what a crinos can wear. All of these restrictions
are in addition to those listed above.

|RKOCrinos may not use shields.
Crinos may only wear greaves as leg armor.
Crinos may only wear armguards, bracelets, and bracers as arm armor.

Crinos may not wear helmets of any kind.
Crinos may not wear torso armor of any kind.
Crinos may not wear boots of any kind.

|BKOExceptions: There are exceptional/special armors throughout the MUD
            that are specifically allowed for crinos use despite
            being restricted normally.
